<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Flashcards Review</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">
</head>
<body>
    <h1 class="animated-title">Review Flashcards</h1>

    <div class="cards-container">
        <div class="card">
            <div class="question">What is HTML?</div>
            <div class="answer">HTML stands for HyperText Markup Language. It is used to structure content on the web.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
            <div class="question">What is CSS?</div>
            <div class="answer">CSS stands for Cascading Style Sheets. It is used to style the HTML content.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
            <div class="question">What is JavaScript?</div>
            <div class="answer">JavaScript is a programming language used to create dynamic and interactive web pages.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
            <div class="question">What is a function in JavaScript?</div>
            <div class="answer">A function is a block of code designed to perform a particular task.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
            <div class="question">What is a variable in programming?</div>
            <div class="answer">A variable is used to store data that can be referenced and manipulated in a program.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
            <div class="question">What is a loop in programming?</div>
            <div class="answer">A loop is a programming structure that repeats a block of code a certain number of times.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
            <div class="question">What is the DOM?</div>
            <div class="answer">DOM stands for Document Object Model. It represents the structure of a web page's HTML elements.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
            <div class="question">What is responsive web design?</div>
            <div class="answer">Responsive web design ensures web pages look good and function properly on all screen sizes and devices.</div>
        </div>
    </div>

</body>
</html>
